<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued January 07 at 10:46AM MST until January 08 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Albuquerque</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 2 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 8
AM MST MONDAY...
* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 5 inches.
Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.
* WHERE...Glorieta Mesa Including Glorieta Pass.
* WHEN...From 2 PM this afternoon to 8 AM MST Monday.
* IMPACTS...Plan on snow packed or icy road conditions. This
includes portions of I-25.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling. For the latest road
conditions, dial 511 or 1.800.432.4269, or visit http://nmroads.com.</instruction>
